description: More than 8,000 continental islands sit just off the coast of Australia, many of them uninhabited and unspoiled. For thousands of species, these patches of habitat offer refuge from the threats they face on the mainland.
title: Old botanical surveys help researchers track how plants on Australia's islands are changing

description: One of the Holy Grails in cosmology is a look back at the earliest epochs of cosmic history. Unfortunately, the universe's first few hundred thousand years are shrouded in an impenetrable fog. So far, nobody's been able to see past it to the Big Bang. As it turns out, astronomers are chipping away at that cosmic fog by using data from the Atacama Cosmology Telescope (ACT) in Chile.
title: Bridging the gap between the cosmic microwave background and the first galaxies

description: The clearest and most precise images yet of the universe in its infancy—the earliest cosmic time accessible to humans—have been produced by an international team of astronomers.
title: Astronomers unveil 'baby pictures' of the first stars and galaxies

description: Children are always asking "Why?" As they experience things for the first time, it's natural to want to find out more. But as children grow into adults, they often dismiss something new that challenges their experience and understanding.
title: Team discovers 'dark oxygen' on the seafloor

description: There is something special about sharing baked goods with family, friends and colleagues. But I'll never forget the disappointment of serving my colleagues rhubarb muffins that had failed to rise. They were dense, rubbery and an embarrassment to the reputation of chemists as good cooks (#ChemistsWhoCook feeds on social media are full of delicious food).
title: What's the difference between baking powder and baking soda? It's subtle, but significant

description: In the remnant rainforests of coastal far-north Queensland, bushwalkers may be lucky enough to catch a glimpse of a diminutive marsupial that's the last living representative of its family.
title: Researches find the only kangaroo that doesn't hop—and it can teach us how roos evolved their quirky gait

description: In recent years, some large physics experiments worldwide have been trying to gather evidence of a nuclear process known as neutrinoless double beta (0νββ) decay. This is a rare process that entails the simultaneous decay of two neutrons in a nucleus into two protons, without resulting in the emission of neutrinos, which is instead associated with standard double beta decay.
title: AMoRE experiment sets new limits on neutrinoless double beta decay of ¹⁰⁰Mo

description: Dogs have many jobs, but one you may not expect is identifying grapevines coated in a destructive and highly contagious fungus. Although dogs can detect serious vine infections by smell, scientists don't know exactly what odor molecules are triggering the response.
title: Guardians of the vineyard: Canines and chemistry work to combat powdery mildew
